==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Broken-backed
<hw>Bro"ken-backed`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a broken back; <as>as, a <ex>broken-backed</ex>
chair</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Hogged; so weakened in the frame
as to droop at each end; -- said of a ship.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Broken-bellied</ent>⟦br⟧
